# Apply Guide

## 1) DB
Run ALL sql/*.sql in Supabase SQL editor.

Minimum to start:
- driver_presence.sql
- order_offers.sql
- order_events.sql
- push_tokens.sql
- idempotency_keys.sql
- job_queue.sql

If you will handle money:
- payments_ledger.sql

## 2) Server routes
Add API routes:
- /api/health -> server/api/health.js
- /api/worker/run -> server/api/worker_run.js
- /api/payments/ledger/transfer -> server/api/payments_ledger_transfer.js

And ensure your existing routes still work.

## 3) Env
- SUPABASE_URL
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
- WORKER_SECRET  (random long string)
- FCM_SERVER_KEY (if you use legacy send endpoint)
- OSRM_BASE_URL  (optional road routing)

## 4) Worker
Call /api/worker/run periodically (cron) with header x-worker-secret.
Example frequency: every 15 seconds for dispatch; every minute for push retries.

## 5) Idempotency usage
For critical actions (create order, accept offer, charge payment):
- Client sends header: Idempotency-Key: <uuid>
- Server wraps handler with withIdempotency()